    "updated_at": "2017-02-15T10:36:46Z",
    "body": "> Because the tabs that Cocoa renders don't actually work in any usable way with Electron right now. This menu item is basically, \"Please draw incorrect crap on my window\".\r\n\r\nUNLESS you open two (or more) folders using command line `atom .` and have atom in fullscreen - then there are pretty useful native tabs that just work: \r\n\r\n![](https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/s/ynjbdtmqtc4rbpi/2017-02-15%20at%2011.36.png)"
