    "created_at": "2017-02-16T03:10:36Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-02-16T03:12:43Z",
    "body": "In Atom's case (and probably most other apps too) it only would make sense to have the tab bar if the native title bar is also shown. Otherwise when using a dark theme, the dark text of the tabs is not legible. And also when the window is not focused, the inactive tab gets a grey background:\r\n\r\n![screen shot 2017-02-16 at 12 00 32 pm](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/378023/23005527/0d21528a-f440-11e6-9b04-1328b10ada23.png)\r\n\r\nSo if any of these [frameless window options](http://electron.atom.io/docs/api/frameless-window/) are set:\r\n\r\n- `frame: false`\r\n- `titleBarStyle: 'hidden'`\r\n- `titleBarStyle: 'hidden-inset'`\r\n\r\nthen don't allow the tab bar, otherwise (with the native title bar) it should be fine:\r\n\r\n![screen shot 2017-02-16 at 12 12 12 pm](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/378023/23005748/3495d718-f441-11e6-9995-d163b16fbd29.png)\r\n"
  },
